SIMPLE: flytrap
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: flytrap
<hw>fly"trap</hw> <pr>(fl⟦imac⟧"tr⟦acr⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A trap for catching flies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A plant <spn>(Dion⟦ae⟧a
muscipula)</spn>, called also <altname>Venus's flytrap</altname>, having
two-lobed leaves which are fringed with stiff bristles, and fold
together when certain sensitive hairs on their upper surface are
touched, thus trapping insects that light on them. The insects so caught
are afterwards digested by a secretion from the upper surface of the
leaves. The plant is native to North and South Carolina, growing in
bogs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>flywheel</ent>⟦br⟧
